observations.recommendation:
We recommended and the Municipal Accountant agreed to:

Undertake efforts to retrieve supporting documents of prior year’s balances of the accounts Due to NGAs and Due to LGUs;
Reconcile the negative balances of the subsidiary ledgers of Due to NGAs and Due to LGUs account totaling ₱19.723 million, and make adjusting entries, if warranted.

We recommended and the Management agreed to:
Identify impediments and challenges affecting the implementation of planned PPAs and develop solutions to address these issues;
Ensure that the development projects funded by the 20% Development Fund are well-planned, procurement- and implementation-ready, and properly coordinated with the concerned departments;
Direct the Municipal Planning and Development Office to collaborate closely with the Municipal Engineering Office, and to regularly monitor the implementation of the targeted development projects funded out of 20% DF; and
Prioritize the full and timely utilization of the 20% Development Fund so that intended beneficiaries receive the services and benefits envisioned under the funded projects.

We recommended and the management agreed to: instruct the Municipal Accountant and HRMO to:

Initiate the establishment of policy and guidelines in the selection and recruitment of Job Order personnel;

Specify the duties and responsibilities of each personnel in the Job Order Contract;

Ensure that all disbursements are properly authorized and approved for payment.

We recommended and the management agreed that:
The LCE require the Inventory Committee to prepare and submit the RCPPE in a required format;
The Municipal Accountant and the designated Property Custodian maintain the required PPE Ledger Cards and Property Cards respectively;
The Municipal Accountant reconcile the record of the CIP account and to reclassify the cost of completed projects to the appropriate PPE accounts; and
The Municipality avail of the one-time cleansing of PPE accounts as provided under COA Circular No. 2020-006 to finally establish PPE balances that are verifiable as to existence, condition and accountability.

We recommended and the management agreed that the LCE:
Ensure that the Engineering Office properly schedule the implementation of its projects;
Require the Barangay to submit requirements to avail benefits that could have been derived from the socio-economic development projects;
Revisit the proposed projects that were not implement and re-evaluate the project and propose re-alignment for projects that can be implemented; and
Ensure that all development projects shall be implemented during the year as embodied in the Annual Development Plan in accordance with the guidelines set in RA No. 7160 and DILG-DOF-DBM JMC No.1 dated November 4, 2020.

We recommended that the LCE ensure that Municipal Accountant:

Exhaust all means to retrieve the necessary data/documents for immediate recording in the books of account, of all identified reconciling items;

Draw journal vouchers to record all valid reconciling items that require adjustment and correction in the GL promptly for fair presentation in the FS;

Communicate and reconcile with the bank the identified erroneous charges;

Prepare and submit immediately the bank reconciliation statements for the various bank accounts as of December 31, 2020, and every month thereafter, to be able to identify and effect the necessary adjusting/correcting entries, if any; and

Together with the Acting Municipal Treasurer, identify and gather documents as evidence for the existence of the unidentified Savings Account.

We recommended that the LCE ensure that the Municipal Accountant:

Observe the proper recording of the reciprocal accounts, Due from Other Funds and Due to Other Funds in order not to increase the unreconciled balances;

Reconcile the reciprocal accounts of all funds maintained by the Municipality, by identifying the causes of discrepancies in the corresponding subsidiary accounts and to effect immediate adjustments in the books of accounts;

Regular reconciliation of the accounts shall be made to ensure the accuracy of the reciprocal accounts:


File all necessary documents for proper documentation; and



Exhaust all means to retrieve the necessary data/documents to reconcile the prior years’ discrepancies and make adjustments.

We recommended that the LCE direct the concerned officials and employees to:

Facilitate the timely submission of the Program and Training Designs and project proposals for the GAD PPAs;

Ensure that budget allocation for GAD is fully utilized in providing adequate assistance, facilities and services to address gender issues in the Municipality; 

Formulate/propose other programs/activities relevant to the projects and with long-term favorable effect to their constituents; and

Strictly adhere to the provisions of JMC No. 2013-01 of the PCW, DILG, DBM and NEDA.
